bill of purchase, bank account details of suppliers or transaction for processing that does not arise from your sale of goods or service to a customer.<br />\r\n <br />\r\n 5.2.2.Acting as a payment intermediary or aggregator or otherwise resell the Services on behalf of any third party.<br />\r\n <br />\r\n 5.2.3.Sending what you believe to be fraudulent authorizations or transaction.<br />\r\n <br />\r\n 5.2.4.Using Service in a manner that any bank reasonably believes to be an abuse of the Banking guidelines by Reserve Bank of India.<br />\r\n <br />\r\n <br />\r\n <br />\r\n <strong>6.Intellectual Property rights</strong><br />\r\n <br />\r\n You acknowledge and agree that the Company (or Company&#39;s licensors) owns all legal right, title and interest in and to the Services, including any intellectual property rights which subsist in them (whether registered or not) and that you are merely a licensee of the Services.<br />\r\n <br />\r\n 6.1.Unless the Company has given you specific written permission to do so, you may not assign (or grant a sub-license of) your rights to use the Service or otherwise transfer any part of your rights to use the Service.<br />\r\n <br />\r\n <br />\r\n <br />\r\n <strong>7.Exclusion of Warranties</strong><br />\r\n <br />\r\n 7.1.You expressly understand and agree that your use of the offering is at your sole risk and that the Services are provided as is and as available.<br />\r\n <br />\r\n 7.2.No advice or information, whether oral or written, obtained by you from the Company or through or from the Services shall create any warranty not expressly stated in the terms.<br />\r\n <br />\r\n <br />\r\n <br />\r\n <strong>8.Limitation of Liability</strong><br />\r\n <br />\r\n 8.1.You expressly understand and agree that the Company shall not be liable to you for any direct, indirect, incidental, special, consequential or exemplary damages which may be incurred by you under the alleged cause of any loss of profit, goodwill, and the like arising out of the usage of Application.<br />\r\n <br />\r\n <br />\r\n <br />\r\n <strong>9.General legal Terms</strong><br />\r\n <br />\r\n 9.1.Sometimes when you use the Services, you may use a service or download a piece of software, or purchase goods, which are provided by another person or company, your use of which shall be at your discretion and the Company assumes no responsibility in this regard.<br />\r\n <br />\r\n 9.2.If any court of law, having the jurisdiction to decide on this matter, rules that any provision of these terms is invalid, then that provision will be removed from the terms without affecting the rest of the terms. The remaining provisions of the terms will continue to be valid and enforceable.<br />\r\n <br />\r\n 9.3.The terms, and your relationship with Company under the terms, shall be governed by the laws of India, and in particular the laws of the State of Delhi. You and Company agrees that any dispute will be referred to arbitration, with the arbitral panel as may be constituted by the High Court of Delhi upon an application in this regard being preferred by any of the parties. The seat and venue of arbitration shall be Delhi and the proceedings shall be governed by the Arbitration &amp; Conciliation Act, 1993.</p>\r\n \r\n <p><strong>Privacy Policy</strong><br />\r\n <br />\r\n Xtracap Fintech India Pvt Ltd (the "Owner"), the owner of the domain "<a href="www.bridge2capital.com" style="color:blue">www.bridge2capital.com</a>" (the "Website") values the users of our Website. Your privacy and trust are very important to us. We recognize that you may be concerned about our collection, use, and disclosure of the personally identifiable information ("Personal Information") that we collect when you use the Website and the services offered on the Website. This Privacy Policy describes the information that we collect from you, how we collect this information, and what we do with it after we collect it. By using the Website you are accepting the practices described in this Privacy Policy. By using the Website you also give consent to use the Personal Information in accordance with the terms set out in this Privacy Policy. If you have any questions or comments regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at <a href="mailto:info@xtracapindia.com" style="color:blue">info@xtracapindia.com</a>. You may mark the mail to the grievance officer at <a href="mailto:info@xtracapindia.com" style="color:blue">info@xtracapindia.com</a>. </p>\r\n \r\n <p>You agree that we may also use Customer Information for the purpose of statistical analysis and for the creation of data ("Statistical Information"). In addition to the information that is elicited from you, you are free to volunteer any other information that you feel that the Owner needs to know, but the security and confidentiality as per this Policy are guaranteed only to the information that the Owner directly asks from you. </p>\r\n\r\n <p>This Policy holds true for a non-customer who has provided information to the Owner, by any means, with the intention of establishing a relationship, of whatsoever nature, with the Owner. By divulging any information to us you agree to the terms and conditions of this Policy. </p>\r\n \r\n <p><strong>USE OF CUSTOMER INFORMATION / STATISTICAL INFORMATION</strong><br />\r\n <br />\r\n We may use the Customer Information for, among other things, customer verification, Know your customer, financial heath check, underwriting, provision of products and services, for personalization of products or services, marketing or promotion of our financial services or related products or that of our associates and affiliates; for creation of Statistical Information, statistical analysis or credit scoring, enforcement of your obligations, any other purpose that will help us in providing you with optimal and high quality services. </p>\r\n \r\n <p><strong>SECURITY</strong><br />\r\n <br />\r\nWe have taken reasonable measures to protect security and confidentiality of the Customer Information and its transmission through the World Wide Web. You are required to follow the Terms and Conditions while using this Website including the instructions stated therein in respect of security and confidentiality of your Log-in and Password. The Owner will give access to Customer Information to only authorized employees.</p>\r\n \r\n <p><strong>CREDIT SCORE</strong><br />\r\n <br />\r\n I hereby appoint Bridge2capital as my authorised representative to receive my credit information from Equifax(Credit bureau).<br />\r\n <br />\r\n I hereby unconditionally consent to and instruct bureau to provide my credit information to me and Bridge2Capital on request submitted via Bridge2Capital app from time to time.<br />\r\n <br />\r\n By submitting this request via Bridge2Capital app I hereby authorize Bridge2Capital to access my credit worthiness and recommend my application NBFC/Bank for working capital assistance for my shop. I also agree that the assistance will be provided solely on discretion of the NBFC/Bank and submission of credit information from Equifax via Bridge2Capital by me doesn&rsquo;t automatically qualify you for a working capital.</p>\r\n \r\n <p><strong>DISCLOSURE</strong>\r\n <ul style="list-style-type:disc; font-family:AvenirLTStd-Book; margin-left:25px">\r\n    <li>We shall not be held liable for disclosure of Customer Information or Statistical Information in accordance with this Privacy Commitment or in terms of any other agreements with you.</li>\r\n    <li>We may disclose the Statistical Information to any person, without any limitation and you hereby give your irrevocable consent for the same. </li>\r\n    <li>We may disclose Customer Information to any of our associates and affiliates without any limitation and you hereby give your consent for the same. </li>\r\n    <li>We may disclose the Customer Information to third parties, without limitation, for the following reasons and you hereby 